  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 10 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 2 critical, 12 high, 16 medium, 9 normal. Key bases needing attention include London Luton (LTN/EGGW), London Gatwick (LGW/EGKK) and Belgrade Nikola Tesla (BEG/LYBE); plus 11 other bases. 16 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is snow-related runway contamination risk, mist and fog / freezing fog  — most notably around Gdańsk Lech Wałęsa (GDN/EPGD), Warsaw Chopin (WAW/EPWA) and London Luton (LTN/EGGW). Network hotspots: Hamburg Helmut Schmidt (HAM/EDDH), Frankfurt-Hahn (HHN/EDFH), Lennart Meri Tallinn (TLL/EETN), Eindhoven (EIN/EHEH), Billund (BLL/EKBI) and 5 others. Primary drivers: low cloud base, mist and cold‑temperature performance penalties. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 3 airports changed status, led by Eindhoven (EIN/EHEH), Shirak (LWN/UDSG), Almaty (ALA/UAAA).",
